  <bioghist id="aspace_72737e0ccf1d7172eb792b8724d71c46">
    <head>BIOGRAPHICAL NOTE</head>
<p>Thomas E. Gee, d.1796, was quartermaster sergeant in Col. John Lamb's regiment of artillery, a detachment from which, commanded by Capt. Wool, was attached to Clinton's brigade during the Sullivan expedition.</p>  </bioghist>
  <scopecontent id="aspace_1546ea7102a4ec6e512e356ac2b11390">
    <head>COLLECTION DESCRIPTION</head>
<p>Orderly book, Aug. 27-Oct. 26, 1779, of Sullivan's campaign kept by Thomas Gee; correspondence, 1803-1934, concerning Thomas Gee, taxes, and his heirs; transcription, photocopy, and photos of the orderly book; photocopies and photographs of Thomas Gee's military service record and other legal documents; Gee family genealogy and family tree; correspondence with historical societies, libraries, archives, and genealogical societies concerning the compilation of the Gee genealogy, from Henrietta Gee McFarlane; paper by Mrs. McFarland, "Frontier Fort,"; and photographs including Gee family gravestones and the graveyard at St. Andrew's Cemetery, Walden, N.Y., where many Gee family members were buried. Also, commission, discharge, and land grant, 1777-1790.</p>  </scopecontent>
  <prefercite id="aspace_a26c4fdadb13ebe22ad52cf30d71edcf">
    <head>Cite As:</head>
<p>Gee family papers, #4176. Division of Rare and Manuscript Collections, Cornell University Library.</p>  </prefercite>
